Today, let’s celebrate @cdrewu, an important part of #CA44’s history.

Founded after the Watts Rebellion of 1965, the university is named after Dr. Charles R. Drew, a renowned Black physician celebrated for his work in blood preservation.  #BlackHistory #Juneteenth https://t.co/EsNvkTmCS4

A day after the funeral, Philonise Floyd came to DC to demand #justice for his brother #GeorgeFloyd.

Philonise testified, "If his death ends up changing the world for the better & I think it will…it is on you to make sure his death isn’t in vain.”
 
It's on us. We must act now. https://t.co/AR0GJc9kyA

#BreonnaTaylor was an award-winning EMT. An aspiring nurse. A friend.
